t2150.text: So I guess the point to this story is that mum and dad spun and extremely elaborate story. I believed it for 10 years because apparently I live under a rock.

t2151.text: That whole time, I thought uncle Stephen had this rude friend called Mick Who stole his car. Turns out he was a repo guy. How on earth could I have been so oblivious? I just believed them and didn’t question it too deeply.

t2152.text: About six months later, I asked why Mick never gave back The car and dad told me not to ask too many questions. He said it was rude so I stopped asking. I didn’t find out the real story until 10 years later.

t2153.text: I still thought that was weird and made no sense but I didn’t question it. Mum invited the guy inside so he must be a friend. She wouldn’t invite a stranger inside which she? That was my eight year old logic anyway.

t2154.text: If Mick was already told that he could borrow the car, why did uncle Stephen seem so annoyed about it? That made no sense. I told dad that and he said Mick wanted the car for a fishing trip. Last time that happened, it stank of fish for weeks so uncle Stephen wasn’t keen on that.

t2155.text: According to dad, Mick had no car so he needed to borrow someone else’s. Something about that explanation didn’t sit right with me. Uncle Stephen came out yelling:“You’re not taking my fucking car! Who do you fucking think you are?!”

t2156.text: I was about eight when this happened. My uncle lived with us and one day, he got his car repossessed. Mum invited the repo guy in for a cup of tea because he looked cold. I asked why that man was taking his car. Dad said it was uncle Stephen’s friend Mick borrowing it.https://twitter.com/adribbleofink/status/1213293516148707328 …

t5703.text: Maybe it’s horrible to say this but I’m relieved it won’t be in the church. The Catholic Church hasn’t always been kind to trans people and I don’t think I would’ve been very comfortable there. I would never have said anything because it’s not my place.

t5704.text: Gran’s siblings are religious but they are the judgemental kind. I suspect they will have a lot of opinions about my transition and that won’t be fun they’ll also be pissed that the funeral isn’t in the Catholic Church. That will be loads of fun. Bleh!

t5705.text: Am I going to have to wear a dress to the funeral? Will I constantly be dead named The whole time? They might do that so the other family members don’t get upset. How the ever living fuck do I deal with that? Where do I go from here?

t5706.text: Oh and speaking of family, I don’t know if me transitioning is going to cause any drama. There are some of them who I haven’t met so I’m not sure if they even know I exist. There are others who I met yonks ago before I even transition. I’m not sure what they will think.

t5708.text: I’m not passing judgement on them not turning up because it’s not my place. I don’t know the situation. There’s a lot of complicated crap going on and I don’t want to be caught in the middle of it.
